  "d/dx[f(g(x))] = f'(g(x))": "",
  "The chain rule states that the derivative of a composite function f(g(x)) is f'(g(x)) * g'(x). You differentiate the outer function evaluated at the inner function, then multiply by the derivative of the inner function.": "",
  "What does 'composite function' mean?": "",
